{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"7fc094c5f01526c965e541ec82007c487f6fa288"},"timestamp":1572601662,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU1MTYwMTI5MTM=","github-url":"https://github.com/hexatomic/hexatomic/issues/73","origin":"github"},"title":"Improve bugfix/hotfix workflow","message":"We may want to differentiate between bug fixes from external users and hotfixes by maintainers.\n\nHotfixes would follow the GitFlow hotfix workflow.\n\nBug fixes could just be features, and released as/collected in a feature release.\n\nIf we wanted to stick as close as possible to GitFlow, we could ask people to use any old branch for a bug fix, then start the hotfix workflow locally, and merge their branch into the hotfix, solving conflicts ourselves (as the maintainer), etc. This would IMHO be the better option, separate bug fixes, and automate SemVer compatibility a bit better.\n\nOr, they just submit a PR as a feature, and we simply follow the feature release workflow. In which case using `mvn gitflow:feature-start` would have pulled in the wrong version bump, i.e., in minor rather than patch.\n\nPerhaps we could just have both scenarios.\n\nSuggestion: Set this up in a fork, try all options, then decide.","files":null}]}